From: Nickel Browser Team <team@nickel-browser.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] nickel: vpn-layer — OS-level proxy routing for VPN tabs

Add a VPN proxy layer that routes traffic for VPN-enabled tabs through
a user-configured SOCKS5 or HTTP proxy (or the Nickel-provided VPN
endpoint when available).

For the MVP this wraps the existing Chromium proxy infrastructure so
no kernel driver or TUN adapter is needed.  A full kernel-level VPN
(WireGuard / OpenVPN) is tracked in a separate issue.

Architecture:
  NickelVPNService  — manages the VPN proxy configuration
  NickelVPNTabHelper — per-tab helper that applies the VPN proxy
---
